@meta
title: Checkout Core Spec
version: 0.1
owner: ai-agent
authority: source
doc_base_path: 

@map
- CORE-000 | Input Guide | Quick rules for what to fill in this document
- CORE-001 | Problem and Goal | Define the problem, target metrics, and success criteria
- CORE-010 | Core User/Service Flow | Merge PRD intent and service logic into one flow
- CORE-020 | Technical Decisions and Constraints | Capture ADR-level decisions and constraints
- CORE-030 | AI Work Rules and Approval Gate | Define mandatory AI execution and approval rules

@section CORE-000
title: Input Guide
summary: Minimum input rules for consistent writing by humans and AI
links: GUIDE-INPUT
content:
<<<
[Required input]
1) Fill every blank after -, 1), and : with concrete content.
2) Use specific numbers, dates, owners, and evidence whenever possible.
3) If unknown, do not leave blank; write TBD (needs confirmation).

[AI request contract]
- target_docs: actual file path
- target_sections: section IDs or section paths
- goal: why this change is needed (1-2 sentences)
- constraints: scope/forbidden constraints
- done: validation-based completion criteria

[AI output contract]
- Changed files / Changed sections / Reason / Impact / Risks / Validation

[Done checklist]
- Are @map rows and @section IDs aligned?
- For edits, is @change reason/impact recorded?
>>>

