@section CORE-010
title: Core User/Service Flow
summary: Keep user scenario and backend flow in one coherent path
links: FLOW-CORE-001
content:
<<<
[Core user scenario]
1) entry condition:
2) key action:
3) expected output:

[Service processing steps]
1) input validation
2) domain processing
3) external integrations
4) persistence and response
>>>

@section CORE-020
title: Technical Decisions and Constraints
summary: Record high-cost technical decisions and hard constraints
links: ADR-CORE-001
content:
<<<
[Key decisions]
1) decision:
   - rationale:
   - alternatives:

[Constraints]
- performance:
- security/policy:
- operations:
>>>

@section CORE-030
title: AI Work Rules and Approval Gate
summary: Define mandatory AI request fields and approval checks
links: AIGATE-CORE-001
content:
<<<
[Required fields for AI request]
- target document:
- target sections:
- reason:
- impact:
- done criteria:

[Approval gate]
1) if service logic changes, source doc must be updated first
2) reject when @change(reason/impact) is missing
3) reject when validation checklist is incomplete
>>>

